My thirst for knowledge constantly forces me to jump into new environments and explore new ideas! My passion for writing code and learning new programming languages could potentially fit under the heading “Addictions”, but the university wouldn't let me keep that in my resume.

bio:
# Project / Program Manager

### Business Intelligence * Web Development * Life Sciences

Enthusiastic and entrepreneurial professional with results-charged career leading complex online and offline technology projects impacting enterprise-wide information technology, sales, and marketing programs across multiple industries. Strong analyzer, strategic planner, and decisive leader with proven success developing emerging concepts into full-fledged, high-performance realities that reduce costs, boost profits, and build corporate value.

# Key Strengths

* Full-Cycle Project & Program Management 
* Web 2.0 & AJAX Technology Development 
* Vendor Management 
* Technology Solutions & Integration 
* Marketing Analytics & Campaign Metrics 
* Business Intelligence & Data Warehousing  
* Quality Control & Improvement 
* Enterprise Documentation & Reporting 
* Multiple Product Line Enhancement 
* Strong Presenter & Communicator 
* Cross-Functional Team Leadership 
* Critical Thinker & Problem Solver  

# Professional Experience

### The Open Domain

*Co-Principal, April 2009 - Present*

Co-founded a philanthropic social venture to increase public awareness of Linux and open software. Led the technical development with a PHP, Javascript, MySQL, Linux, and CSS architecture in an agile (Scrum) environment. Serves as co-director of the initiative on a volunteer basis, overseeing strategy, business development, and marketing.

* Created strategic marketing plan to produce web traffic at 3 million page views per month by Q4 2010. 
* Formulated technical strategy to build an enhanced, next-generation Web experience grounded in personal customization.  

### National Not-For-Profit Health Management Organization

*Project Manager (Contractor), 2 years*

Led bottom-line-driven marketing, business intelligence, and reporting projects using agile methodologies that support multiple business lines for a non-profit managed care organization with $35B in annual revenue. Oversaw the lifecycle process from initial planning, design, and target mapping through execution, delivery, and market launch. Analyzed corporate goals and ensured each project and program met benchmarks. Facilitated business process analysis workshops to document and understand “as-is” and “to be” marketing and communications processes.

* Decreased campaign set-up time 90% and increased conversion 10% by driving process and reporting improvements and managing solution aspects of multi-channel / multi-wave lead management and nurturing program for new online / offline leads. 
* Directed a $1M interim business management, management reporting, and marketing analytics solution for the individual and family plans line of business.  
* Created and proposed a set of comprehensive program and project management processes, procedures, and protocols affecting database marketing projects.  
* Partnered with internal and vendor development and testing teams in design and development of ETL processes and data models for the data warehouse and analytical data stores. 
* Aligned operations for a 2% lift forecast in conversion for all lines of business after defining and designing deliverables for a $20M marketing data warehouse supporting customer relationship management directives.  
* Managed analysts and developers to review and analyze business systems and user needs  leading to innovative solutions that seized the latest opportunities 
* Made proactive recommendations that drove key performance goals, such as reducing cost per lead (CPL) and cost per member (CPM) on both acquisition and retention fronts. 
* Worked consultatively with project stakeholders and key business users to formulate solutions that paralleled our overall marketing strategy.  

### Medical Cost-Containment & Healthcare Risk Management Company

*Manager, Information Systems, 2 years*

Delivered information systems projects for a $10M provider of medical cost-containment and healthcare risk management services to the insurance market. Managed a cross-functional team and led the full software development lifecycle (SDLC) of offline and web-based applications supporting business intelligence and customer relationship management goals. Spearheaded the adoption of Agile development methodologies leading to accelerated application development. Partnered with end-users and key stakeholders in analyzing business systems and needs to create solutions that reflect business strategies.

* Decreased product line service costs and instituted process enhancements of the hospital file audit and bill review lines of business through close management of a Java-based bill review and pricing analytics system that utilizes first-party and third-party data. 
* Defined and designed a proprietary Customer Relationship Management (CRM) solution to improve the management of promotions as well as the marketing and sales response process. 
* Increased product quality and drove client satisfaction levels after managing a quality analytics system and implementing tracking / reporting capabilities pertaining to hospital file audits. 
* Presented business and technical strategy to internal clients and external vendors and facilitated technology strategy sessions to improve and automate business processes. 
* Led the definition and design phases of medical record review tracking and web-based document management applications designed to decrease product line service costs and automate internal business processes.  

### Elementary School District

*Contractor, 2 years*

Led web-based, LAMP-powered e-learning platform projects using agile development methodologies for a K-8 school district with more than 500 employees across 10 traditional and three charter schools. Analyzed educational needs and outlined scope of project to meet objectives.  

* Facilitated weekly instruction programs on web programming and graphical user interface (GUI) design and development. 
* Bridged in-class and home-based instruction by spearheading the SDLC of an interactive “Courseware” system for a life-science-based charter school. 
* Analyzed educational needs to determine scope, requirements, and objectives of internal and external web-based software applications to further educational and promotional objectives.  

### The James David Company

*Co-Principal, 4 years*

Served as Co-Principal of web services business in an entrepreneurial and client-facing role. Accountable for leading agile web services projects for a solution design and consulting firm specializing in consumer-facing web-based applications that enhance marketing and sales directives. Oversaw the entire lifecycle development process from initial conception and design through implementation and finalization of LAMP-stacked web applications.

* Led major web development projects in a hands-on fashion using agile development methodologies including, but not limited to, Condominium Reservation System, National Restaurant Review, Small Business Networking, and Website / Content Management Systems. 
* Collaborated with international clients and analyzed business and user needs to develop innovated web applications that furthered direct marketing initiatives and yielded a more efficient “call to action”. 
* Managed the participated in the development of customer-facing LAMP (Linux-Apache-MySQL-PHP) content-management applications.

I went to school to study Philosophy - and graduated with a B. A. in that subject. A month after graduation I took a job in web development.
